  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7105 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 7115 (-3934M) and the massive positive gamma wall at 7100 (+5111M), dealers are likely in flow-balancing mode, neither aggressively buying nor selling into this tight range. The PIN regime with 56.6B total GEX suggests dealers will sell any push toward the 7150-7200 resistance zone where positive gamma exceeds +6B, while providing support on dips toward 7100. Key levels to watch: 7100 support (dealers buy), 7115 amplification zone (momentum risk), and 7150-7200 resistance (dealers sell rallies).\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy, range-bound action between 7100-7150 with dealers capping upside moves.",
